    <item>
      <title>Fixed Size Window</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/tracks/fixed-size-window/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 26 Apr 2026 13:06:31 +0530</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/tracks/fixed-size-window/</guid>
      <description>A sliding window approach where the window size remains constant throughout the iteration. Commonly used for problems like maximum sum subarray of size k or average of subarrays.</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Variable Size Window</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/tracks/variable-size-window/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 26 Apr 2026 13:06:31 +0530</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/tracks/variable-size-window/</guid>
      <description>A flexible sliding window where the size expands or shrinks based on a given condition. Useful for problems like longest substring or subarray satisfying a constraint.</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Variable Size Window Plus Hashmap</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/tracks/variable-size-window-plus-hashmap/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 26 Apr 2026 13:06:31 +0530</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/tracks/variable-size-window-plus-hashmap/</guid>
      <description>Enhances variable windows by using a hash map to track element frequency or presence. Essential for solving problems like longest substring without repeating characters or anagram matching.</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Window Plus Monotonic Deque</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/tracks/window-plus-monotonic-deque/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 26 Apr 2026 13:06:31 +0530</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/tracks/window-plus-monotonic-deque/</guid>
      <description>Combines sliding window with a deque that maintains elements in sorted order (monotonic). Used to efficiently find maximum or minimum values in a window in O(n) time.</description>
    </item>
